@node "New"

@toc "Process menu"

@{U}1.4.1  New [F6/7/8/9]                                  PHOENIX Manager@{u}



This command is used to create a new query [F6], a new report [F7],

a new calculation [F8], a new batch [F9] or a new template.



Clicking on the entry opens the @{"New process dialog-box" LINK "Dialogbox Neuer Prozeû"}.



Alternatively, resting the mouse pointer on the menu entry opens a

popup in which the type of window to be created can be selected

directly. A second and often faster alternative (except for template)

is provided by the @{"function key bar" LINK "Schreibtisch des Managers" "Function key bar"} of the Manager's desktop.



@endnode





@node "List"

@toc "Process menu"

@{U}1.4.2  List                                            PHOENIX Manager@{u}



This command is used to display existing queries, existing reports,

existing calculations, existing batches or existing templates.



Clicking on the entry opens the @{"New process dialog-box" LINK "Dialogbox Neuer Prozeû"}. Alternatively,

resting the mouse pointer on the menu entry opens a popup in which

the type of window to be opened can be selected directly.



@endnode





@node "Execute"

@toc "Process menu"

@{U}1.4.3  Execute [X]                                    PHOENIX Manager@{u}



With this command a query, a report, a calculation, a batch or a

template can be executed.



@{U}Query@{u}

If a data record in a @{"query-list window" LINK "Abfrageliste-Fenster"} is selected, then the data

records appropriate to this query will be searched for.



If a @{"query window" LINK "Abfrage-Fenster"} is topped, then the corresponding query will be

executed. The search of the data records runs as a background process,

so that you can continue to work during the search. If sorting is

required, then the data records will be sorted after the search.

Sorting does not run in the background. During this sorting process

a dialog-box provides information about its progress. After the data

records have been searched and sorted, if appropriate, a @{"table window" LINK "Tabellen-Fenster"}

opens automatically which displays the found data records.



A query can be executed only if it does not contain any errors. If

errors occur, this will be reported in an error alert, so giving you

the opportunity to make corrections. The statements in the error alert

refer to the generated SQL command.



@{I}Note:@{i}

The search of data records can proceed quickly or slowly. That depends

on the type of query. The program attempts to obtain the result as

quickly as possible. This succeeds particularly when a query is set

with the equality condition or the BETWEEN condition in an already

existing index.



The time shown in the @{"process window" LINK "Prozeû-Fenster"} is the maximum time for the

search.



@{U}Template@{u}

If a @{"template window" LINK "Report-Fenster"} is topped then this template will be executed.



If a @{"table icon" LINK "Tabellen-Sinnbild"} or data records in a table are selected, then the

Manager attempts to combine these data records with the template,

i.e. to execute the template on these data records. If no items are

selected, then the table specified under {$TABELLE=..} will be used as

the source of data.



A template can be executed only if it does not contain any errors. If

errors occur, this will be reported in an error alert, so giving you

the opportunity to make corrections. The execution of the template

runs as a background process. Before execution of the template you

have to select whether the template is to be output to the @{B}Screen@{b},

the @{B}Printer@{b}, or into a @{B}File@{b}.



@{I}Note:@{i}

If the template is present in the 1st Word Plus format, then it has

to be output to a file, since the Manager can not print the Wordplus

format directly. Nevertheless, the output file of the template retains

the Wordplus attributes (bold, underscored etc.) as well as any incor-

porated graphics. This file can then be printed in the 1st Word Plus

program.



@{U}Calculation@{u}

The calculation is executed as a background process. The data record

set to which a calculation is applied can be defined in various ways:



  1. If no item is selected on the desktop or in a @{"table window" LINK "Tabellen-Fenster"}, then

     the calculation will be performed on all data records of the

     current table of the @{"database toolbox" LINK "Schreibtisch des Managers" "Database toolbox"}.

  2. If a @{"table icon" LINK "Tabellen-Sinnbild"} or a @{"table-clipboard icon" LINK "Tabellenklemmbrett-Sinnbild"} is selected on the

     desktop, then the calculation will be performed on all data

     records of the source of this icon.

  3. If data records in a table window are selected, then the calcula-

     tion will be performed on all selected data records.



For executing a calculation you can also drag a table from the

@{"database toolbox" LINK "Schreibtisch des Managers" "Database toolbox"}, a table icon, or data records from a @{"table window" LINK "Tabellen-Fenster"}

onto the @{"calculation window" LINK "Rechnen-Fenster"}.



@{U}Batch@{u}

If a data record in a @{"batch-list window" LINK "Batchliste-Fenster"} is selected, then the batch

will be executed. If a @{"batch window" LINK "Batch-Fenster"} is topped, then this batch will

be executed.



The processing of a batch runs as a background process, so that you

can continue working during the batch run. Running the batch can nudge

other processes into action. If there are 6 processes running already,

then the batch run will be blocked if it tries to start yet another

process until a process is available to be started again.



@endnode





