@{U}2.1.1  Save (record) [S]                              PHOENIX Manager@{u}



On activating this @{"mask window" LINK "Masken-Fenster"} menu entry, or its icon bar equivalent,

the current data record will be saved.



PHOENIX offers two options for saving a data record:



  1. If a new data record was created, then it will be inserted into

     the table. A new data record can be input by pressing the @{B}@{New ignore}@{b}

     icon (the tabbed index card) or use the command New mask in the

