@node "Search (record)"

@toc "Record menu"

@{U}2.1.4  Search (record) [F]                            PHOENIX Manager@{u}



On activating this @{"mask window" LINK "Masken-Fenster"} menu entry, or its icon bar equivalent,

then if the cursor is over a field that was defined as an index, the

Manager will switch to this field and attempt to find the data record.

If the data record is not found then an error message will be output

and the data record that comes closest to the search term will be

displayed.



It's best to clear the mask beforehand with the New mask command and

enter the search term into the desired field.



You may use the following wildcards:



* represents any character-string (may be empty as well)

? represents just one character of any kind



If the cursor is not over an index field, then Manager switches over

to a "Sequentiell" index and attempts to find the data record sequen-

tially. A largish data cache is particularly favourable here, as each

data record will be read in and searched in turn.



If you want to search in a multi-index, the use the Multi-search

command.



@endnode





