 2.2.2  Back

 2.2.3  Forward

 2.2.4  Start

 2.2.5  End



@endnode





@node "New mask"

@toc "Actions menu"

@{U}2.2.1  New mask [N]                                   PHOENIX Manager@{u}



On activating this @{"mask window" LINK "Masken-Fenster"} menu entry, or its icon bar equivalent,

all fields of a mask will be cleared so that you can compose a new

data record.



Once you have filled in a new record, it can be saved in the table

with the mask window's @{"Insert" LINK "Insert (record)"} or @{"Save" LINK "Save (record)"} commands.



@endnode





@node "Back"

@toc "Actions menu"

@{U}2.2.2  Back [K]                                       PHOENIX Manager@{u}



On activating this @{"mask window" LINK "Masken-Fenster"} menu entry, or its icon bar equivalent,

the mask displays one data record back in the set sorting order.

For the first data record the command is greyed out.



If the sorting order is @{B}Descending@{b}, the position will also be one

record back in the displayed order, which is actually the next higher

record.





@endnode





@node "Forward"

@toc "Actions menu"

@{U}2.2.3  Forward [V]                                    PHOENIX Manager@{u}



On activating this @{"mask window" LINK "Masken-Fenster"} menu entry, or its icon bar equivalent,

the mask displays one data record forwards in the set sorting order.

For the last data record the command is greyed out.



If the sorting order is @{B}Descending@{b}, the position will also be one

record forwards in the displayed order, which is actually the next

lower record.



@endnode





@node "Start"

@toc "Actions menu"

@{U}2.2.4  Start [A]                                      PHOENIX Manager@{u}



On activating this @{"mask window" LINK "Masken-Fenster"} menu entry, or its icon bar equivalent,

the mask displays the first data record according to the set sorting

order.



If the sorting order is @{B}Descending@{b}, this will be actually the

highest data record.



@endnode





@node "End"

@toc "Actions menu"

@{U}2.2.5  End [E]                                        PHOENIX Manager@{u}



On activating this @{"mask window" LINK "Masken-Fenster"} menu entry, or its icon bar equivalent,

the mask displays the last data record according to the set sorting

order.



If the sorting order is @{B}Descending@{b}, this will be actually the lowest

data record.



@endnode





