Below the menu bar lies the info line. This shows the criterium by

which the displayed data records are currently sorted.



The info line of a mask window too can be hidden or revealed in

DESIGNER for each mask individually by using the appropriate checkbox

in the @{Info ignore} function of @{Designer ignore}'s @{"mask window" LINK "DESIGNER.HYP/Dialogbox Masken-Info"}.



@{U}Working area@{u}

This displays the mask and serves for constructing or modifying data

records;  the input will be to the field that contains the cursor,

which can be positioned directly in any desired field with a mouse

click. If this is a Text field, then the cursor will be placed on the

character that was clicked on.



In most cases the cursor will be displayed as a black block. For

graphics fields, @{"BLOB" LINK "DESIGNER.HYP/Data types" 72}'s, radio buttons as well as checkboxes it

will be depicted as a dotted frame (around the field).



If a field is defined as an output field, or if the access protection

@{B}Read only@{b} was defined for the field, then the cursor will jump over

this field. A double-click on a field of the @{"External file" LINK "DESIGNER.HYP/Data types" 40} data type

has the same effect as the Display field command. An attempt will be

made to display the external file in a window, or to replay the sound

if it is a suitable sound sample file.



Left-clicking on a field while holding down the [Alternate] key allows

you to mark fields. The name or label of the field will be displayed

in light type (greyed out). The contents of a marked field is not

deleted after inserting the data record and is available for further

input.



If you want to mark fields of a mask permanently, then you can set

this in DESIGNER in the @{"Field attributes dialog-box" LINK "DESIGNER.HYP/Dialogbox Feldattribute"} with the switch

