@node "Report-list window"

@toc "The windows"

@{U}3.15  Report-list window [F7]                         PHOENIX Manager@{u}



This window opens when you activate ListReport in the Process menu.

It will either be empty, or display the entries of previously prepared

reports and sub-reports. It is a special form of a @{"table window" LINK "Tabellen-Fenster"}.



The title line of the window shows the database used for the report.



Below the title line lies the info line. It shows by which criteria

any displayed reports are currently sorted. On a new report-list this

will be 'Name' and '+' (for ascending order).



If reports and/or sub-reports have been prepared previously, then in

the icon bar under the info line you can change the sorting direction

with the @{B}+@{b} and @{B}-@{b} buttons. The binoculars (Search) icon has no

applications in this window; the mask icon calls the Edit data

function, opening the relevant SYSTEM mask where you can modify the

entries (but normally you will not want to do this).



Under the icon bar is the header line of the table, showing the names

of the columns. Below this the individual reports and sub-reports are

displayed line by line.



The following operations can be performed with the window:



@{U}Iconize@{u}

With the Iconize command of the Edit menu or its equivalent in the

function key bar a table can be converted to a @{"table icon" LINK "Tabellen-Sinnbild"}.



@{U}Selection of reports/sub-reports@{u}

A left mouse-click selects a report entry and displays it in inverse

video.



You can execute all commands on the selected reports that take effect

on reports, although only a few can be applied sensibly.



A double left-click on a report or sub-report opens the @{"Report window" LINK "Bericht-Fenster"}

displaying the individual elements of the report, which can then be

modified if required. A double right-click has the same effect as the

Execute command in the Process menu, creating a preview of the report

in the @{"Preview window" LINK "Vorschau-Fenster"} which can then be printed if desired.



@endnode





@node "Tabellen-Fenster" "Table window"

@toc "The windows"

@{U}3.16  Table window                                     PHOENIX Manager@{u}



A table window can be created with the Open table command of the

Edit menu, amongst others.



The title line of the window shows the database and the table from

which the data records originate.

If the window is a result of a named query, then its name will be

appended within brackets. Should it be an Auto-query, then an excla-

mation mark in brackets '(!)' will be output. An Auto-query is a

query that has the same name as a table.



Below the title line lies the info line. It shows by which criteria

the displayed data records are currently sorted.



In the icon bar under the info line you can change the index in the

listbox and the sorting direction with the @{B}+@{b} and @{B}-@{b} buttons. The other

two icons (the binoculars and the mask respectively) call the Search

and Edit data functions.



Under the icon bar is the header line of the table, showing the names

of the columns. Below this the individual data records are displayed

line by line.



The following operations can be performed with the window:



@{U}Iconize@{u}

With the Iconize command of the Edit menu or its equivalent in the

function key bar a table can be converted to a @{"table icon" LINK "Tabellen-Sinnbild"}.



@{U}Selection and moving of data records@{u}

A left mouse-click selects a data record and displays it in inverse

video. Further data records can be selected by holding down a [Shift]

key, or deselected again the same way.

By pressing and holding down the left mouse button while the mouse

pointer is in the left margin of the table, you can drag out a rubber

band rectangle to select all data records that the rubber banded area

overlays. By holding down a [Shift] key during the operation the

selected data records will be deselected and vice versa.

If you hold down the [Control] key during this you can select some

additional data records.



You can execute all commands on the selected data records that take

effect on data records. In addition, the selected data records can be

dragged onto all items of the Manager's desktop for which an operation

is defined. This is explained in @{"The Manager's desktop" LINK "Schreibtisch des Managers"} section.



A double-click on the selected data records has the same effect as

the Edit data command in the Edit menu. Furthermore the data records

can be dragged to a free place on the desktop, when they will be

converted into a @{"table-clipboard icon" LINK "Tabellenklemmbrett-Sinnbild"}. This will cause the appearance

of the @{"Clipboard name dialog-box" LINK "Dialogbox Klemmbrett-Name"}, where you can assign it another name

to differentiate it from the table name shown by default.



@{U}Changing the column selection@{u}

A column will be removed from the display if you drag the column name

to the wastebin. Alternatively you can just right-click on the column

name to achieve this.



@{U}Changing the column order@{u}

A column can be moved to another position by dragging the column name

to a different place.

Drag to the right: It appears after the column at which the mouse

button was released.

Drag to the left: If appears before the column at which the mouse

button was released.



@{U}Changing the column widths@{u}

Left-click on the vertical separation line between the column headers

and drag the line in the desired direction.  During this a small box

shows the @{B}Width@{b} of the column and the @{B}Total@{b} width. Alternatively you

can double-click either mouse button on the header of a column to

open the @{"Column width dialog-box" LINK "Dialogbox Spaltenbreite"}, where you can set a new width.



@{U}Changing the sorting@{u}

If only the sorting order is to be changed (ascending to descending or

vice versa), then call the Reverse sort command in the Options menu.

If the table is to be displayed sorted by a different index, then this

can be selected in the index listbox popup in the icon bar. With some

windows the sorting order can not be changed.



@{U}Searching@{u}

If you want to jump to a given data record in a table window, then

you have to select the Search command in the Edit menu or click on

the binocular icon. This opens the @{"Search dialog-box" LINK "Dialogbox Suchen"}.



@{I}Note:@{i}

A single column in a table window can have a maximum width of 255

characters. If it is wider, it will be truncated to 255 characters.



@{U}Pictures and BLOBs@{u}

Columns that can not be displayed are replaced by the '*' character.

These types include all images and the @{"BLOBs" LINK "DESIGNER.HYP/Data types" 72}. Columns that overflow

are replaced by the '#' character. An overflow occurs, for instance,

if a format was specified for a Number field in which there is not

enough room to accommodate the current number.



@endnode



