@node "Property: Text"

@toc "The properties"

@xref "The properties"

@{U}4.1.47  Property: Text                                 PHOENIX Manager@{u}



This appears in the @{"properties window" LINK "Eigenschaften-Fenster"} when you double-click on a text

frame. It permits the output of any desired fixed texts that you can

type into the field at the top of the table. The field will scroll

automatically for long texts.



Apart from this, you can also use the Text property for performing

calculations. There are three options for this:



Simple, one-line calculations can be typed in directly. They have to

start with an equality sign ('='). This is particularly useful when

data from various fields have to be collected together, say to build

up the salutation for a letter. If you were to assemble this from

several items, you would probably get some ugly gaps between the

individual objects.



@{I}Example:@{i}

="Sehr geehrte"+Anrede+" "+Vorname+" "+Nachname

or in English:

="Dear"+@{Title ignore}+" "+Forename+" "+Surname



As usual with calculations, fixed texts have to be enclosed in double-

quotes, while the field names can be typed in directly.



More complex calculations have to be input in a @{"calculation window" LINK "Rechnen-Fenster"}

and saved. They are called with the equality sign followed by the '@@'

character and the name of the calculation. The calculation must use

the function RETURN to return the result that is to be inserted into

the report. Further information about this in the @{"calculation window" LINK "Rechnen-Fenster"}

page.



@{I}Example:@{i}

=@@Calculation for report



Short calculations for which it is not really worth while to construct

and save a calculation, but which contain more than one command, can

be accommodated in a Text field via a trick: The equality sign can be

followed also by a complete calculation. This has to be prefaced by a

variable declaration (VAR). This is followed by the individual assign-

ments, separated by a semicolon in each case. At the end there has to

be a RETURN assignment to insert the calculation result into the

report.



@endnode





