@{U}10  Sidebar: SQL                                       PHOENIX Manager@{u}



SQL is a database query language that PHOENIX uses internally. When

you define a query with the mouse and keyboard, PHOENIX converts your

input into an SQL command, which you as a user will not notice.



However, if you are interested how a query looks as an SQL statement,

you only have to select a query in a query-list and then activate the

Edit data command (F10). The query will then appear in the system

mask, where you may even alter the SQL command.



The available SQL commands are listed in Calculation commands.





