@node "Logical operators"

@toc "Calculation commands"

@xref "IF-THEN-ELSE-END"

@{U}A.33  Logical operators: &, |, !                       PHOENIX Manager@{u}



These are used to combine logical values with one another. These

logical values are TRUE for a true declaration and FALSE for an

untrue declaration.



The operator '&' is a logical AND. Its result is TRUE only if both

operands have the value TRUE, otherwise it is FALSE.



The operator '|' is a logical OR. Its result is FALSE only if both

operands have the value FALSE, otherwise it is TRUE.



The logical operator '!' represents a negation. If its operand has

the value TRUE it returns FALSE, otherwise TRUE.



How the logical operators are used you can see in the description of

the IF-THEN-ELSE-END control structure.



@endnode





