@{U}A.41  POSITION                                         PHOENIX Manager@{u}



Searches for a character-string within another character-string.



@{U}Syntax:@{u}

Result=POSITION(Text, searchterm, start);



@{B}Text@{b} is the text to be searched through, @{B}searchterm@{b} is what you are

looking for. The search starts at the position @{B}start@{b} within the text,

where the first character in the text lies at position 0. If the

string searched for is not found, then the function rerturns the

value -1.



@{I}Example:@{i}

POSITION("PHOENIX is wonderful", "is", 0) results in the value 8.



@endnode





