@node "REPEAT-UNTIL"

@toc "Calculation commands"

@{U}A.45  REPEAT-UNTIL                                     PHOENIX Manager@{u}



This is a statement for the programming of a loop. The commands that

follow REPEAT will be repeated until the logical expression following

UNTIL returns the value TRUE. (The difference from WHILE-DO-END is

that the condition is only checked at the end of the loop and hence

the loop is always traversed at least once.)



@{I}Example:@{i}

VAR counter, a;

counter=1; a=10;

REPEAT

  a=a*10; counter=counter+1;

UNTIL counter>10;



This loop will be traversed ten times.



@endnode





