@{B}Result@{b} must be specified for purely syntactic reasons, and can be any

variable or any field. @{B}Value@{b} will be passed to the graphical report.



@{I}Example:@{i}

VAR RetVal;

RetVal = GET ("Text;Country>COUNTRY.Country");

IF Original <> "" THEN

  RetVal = RetVal + ' "' + Original + '"';

END;

IF Copyright <> "" THEN

  RetVal = RetVal + " from the year " + Copyright;

END;

RetVal = RETURN (RetVal);



