@node "Dialogbox Verzweigen" "Branch dialog-box"

@toc "The dialog-boxes"

@autorefoff

@{U}B.1  Branch dialog-box                                 PHOENIX Manager@{u}

@autorefon



The source table is that table of the mask from which branching is

to take place.



The @{B}Source index@{b} listbox displays all indices of the source table

and the @{B}Destination table@{b} listbox all the tables of the database.



The @{B}Destination index@{b} listbox displays all the indices of the table

that are selected with the @{B}Destination table@{b} listbox.



The tables and indices of the 3 listboxes are sorted numerically or

alphabetically, depending on how they appear in the @{"database toolbox" LINK "Schreibtisch des Managers" "Database toolbox"}.



When you activate the @{B}OK@{b} button, at attempt is made to find the value

from the source index in the destination table via the destination

index. A new @{"mask window" LINK "Masken-Fenster"} of the destination table opens.

If the data record was found via the destination index, then Manager

will position on this data record. If the set was not found, then the

positioning will be to the data record that is closest to the destina-

tion index.



The sorting order in the created mask will be set to @{B}Ascending@{b} or

@{B}Descending@{b}, depending how it was chosen with the radio buttons in

the dialog-box.



The selections that are suggested after opening the dialog-box are

preselected according to the definition of the integrity rules. At

best all you have to do is select the @{B}OK@{b} button.



It should be a matter of course that the source and destination

indices should have the same @{"type" LINK "DESIGNER.HYP/Data types"}. You will not be able to branch

successfully if the source index is of the type Number and the

destination index is a Text!



@endnode





