be displayed in the new mask.



@endnode





@node "Dialogbox Paûwort Ñndern" "Change password dialog-box"

@toc "The dialog-boxes"

@autorefoff

@{U}B.3  Change password dialog-box                        PHOENIX Manager@{u}

@autorefon



 @{B}Old password@{b} serves as a check. You have to enter your old password

     into this field. This guarantees that no other user can change

     your password while you are temporarily not in the vicinity of

     your computer.

     The @{B}OK@{b} button is activated only after the last letter of your

     password was entered correctly.



@autorefoff

 @{B}New password@{b} is the field for inputting your new password. As soon

     as this has been input, the @{B}OK@{b} button is deactivated.



 @{B}Verification@{b} serves for checking the password. You have to input the

     new password there in exactly the same way as you did for the

     @{B}New password@{b} field (exception: case is not taken into account).

