@node "Dialogbox Reorganisations-Parameter" "Reorganisation parameters dialog-box"

@toc "The dialog-boxes"

@autorefoff

@{U}B.26  Reorganisation parameters dialog-box             PHOENIX Manager@{u}

@autorefon



This opens after you have activated @{B}OK@{b} in the @{"Reorganise database" LINK "Dialogbox Datenbank reorganisieren"}

dialog-box, having filled out @{B}User@{b} and @{B}Password@{b} if appropriate.



The @{B}Database@{b} line of this dialog-box shows the database that is to be

reorganised.



 ˘ @{B}Reorganise mode@{b} specifies how this database is to be reorganised:



 With @{B}Reset flags@{b} active, only the internal flags will be reset.

     These indicate that the database was not closed correctly, which

     may happen if you lose electrical power, say. This option should

     be chosen only if you are sure that since the time the database

     was last closed it has not been written to, i.e. only read from.



 With @{B}Build index file@{b} active, only those indices will be rebuilt

     that were newly defined in @{Designer ignore}.



 With @{B}Pack data files@{b} active, the data file will be packed and also

     the index file will be rebuilt completely. During packing all

     deleted data records will be lost.



 With the @{B}Encode@{b} checkbox activated, the database will be encrypted

     during reorganisation. This only works with @{B}Pack data files@{b}

     selected in the radio buttons above.



@{I}Note:@{i}

If a serious error occurs during reorganisation, then this process

will be broken off. The original database remains unaltered.



@endnode





