@node "Warnung: Drucker belegt" "Warning: Printer in use"

@toc "Error messages and warnings"

@{U}C.177  Warning: Printer in use                         PHOENIX Manager@{u}



The printer may be accessed only by a single process at a time, as

otherwise the printout would be total confusion. You already have a

process running that is engaging the printer.



You can now select one of the following buttons:



 @{B}Spool@{b}:  The process 'prints' to a file first. This will be put into

         the Printer queue and printed out later.



 @{B}Wait@{b}:   Although the process will be launched, it will be blocked

         immediately. It will be released only when another process

         has released the printer. Then this process prints out

         directly on the printer. As long as a process is lying in

         wait, the @{B}Wait@{b} button is selected and deactivated.



 @{B}Cancel@{b}: The process will not be launched. You must remedy this at

         a later time.



