@node "About PHOENIX"

@toc "Products"

@xref "About Designer"

@xref "About Manager"

@{U}G.2  About PHOENIX                                     PHOENIX Manager@{u}



The database PHOENIX consists of a network-capable database kernel

that can handle all kinds of data (including colour graphics and

sound) of any size. This kernel was adapted specially for requirements

of graphical user interfaces such as GEM and Windows. This enables

super-fast scrolling and display in windows.



Here are some of its performance data:



   ˘ Number of records per database: 2 billion

   ˘ Size per data record: 2 Gigabyte

   ˘ Size of a field per data record: 100 Megabyte

   ˘ Number of tables per database: 32767

   ˘ Number of fields per database: 32767

   ˘ Maximum filesize: 2 Gigabyte = 2048 Megabyte

   ˘ Number of data types per field: 11

   ˘ Index caching for very fast scrolling and searching

   ˘ Data caching for very fast window output

   ˘ Guarantee of referential integrity by the kernel

   ˘ Access protection to database, table and field planes

   ˘ Permanently available context-sensitive help system

   ˘ Freely available graphical formation of masks

   ˘ Number of simultaneously open databases: 8

   ˘ Number of parallel-running processes: 6

   ˘ Query by example

   ˘ Number of clipboards on the desktop: 18

   ˘ Minimum memory requirement: 1.5 MB

   ˘ Runs on ATARIs, Macs with MagiC Mac and PCs with MagiC PC in all

     screen resolutions and with all graphic cards.



The modules DESIGNER and MANAGER are based on the above-mentioned

kernel. DESIGNER is used to lay out the masks common to the whole

database (the equivalent of the labels for the data fields, and their

size and position in a card index - see About Designer).



MANAGER serves for the entry of the actual data for the database, its

evaluation and output of the database contents in a graphical format

(see About Manager).



You can write your own database programs with the aid of a

C-interface (PHOENIX/Base for PureC).



Further information:



About Designer

About Manager



